data.enText: the act of making an official record of sth/sb
the registration of letters and parcels
the registration of students for a course
the registration of a child's birth
a document showing that an official record has been made of sth
the time when a teacher looks at the list of students on the class register and checks that the students are present

tr: the act of adjusting something to match a standard
(music) the sound property resulting from a combination of organ stops used to perform a particular piece of music
the technique of selecting and adjusting organ stops
a document certifying an act of registering
the body of people (such as students) who register or enroll at the same time

value.def: The registration of something such as a person's name or the details of an event is the recording of it in an official list.

example.ex: They have campaigned strongly for compulsory registration of dogs...
example.tran: 他们强烈呼吁实行犬类强制登记。

example.ex: With the high voter registration, many will be voting for the first time.
example.tran: 登记选民数量的上升意味着许多人将第一次参加投票。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to carry, to bring 带来
rootsaffixes.title: gest, gister

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 加强 + gest 带来 → 带来很多 → 充满
di 分开 + gest 带来 → 带下去 → 消化
gest 带来 + iculate 表动作 → 做手势
gest 带来 + ure 表行为 → 能带来信息的动作 → 手势
in 不 + digestion 消化 → 消化不良
re 重新 + gister 带来 → 再次带来〔新来的学生〕→〔学员〕登记，注册
sug 下 + gest 带来 → 从下面带上来〔话〕→ 建议
